<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="A" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Anew" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Anew,</orth> 1) another time, afresh: <bibl n="shak. ven 60" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 60</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. son 119.11" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 119, 11</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. pp 332" default="NO" valid="yes">Pilgr. 332</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 1.1.4" default="NO" valid="yes">All's I, 1, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.3.46" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 3, 46</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.3.42" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 3, 42</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 1.262" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. I, 262</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 4.1.85" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. IV, 1, 85</bibl>.<lb />2) newly, in a new and other manner: <cit><quote>thou art enforced to seek a. some fresher stamp,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 82.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 82, 7</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>and taught it thus a. to greet,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 4.145.8" default="NO" valid="yes">145, 8</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>